ExamplesExplanation3: fc:uwu => Find players in the Free Company 'uwu'.

SearchOptionsExplanation: Use these options to narrow your search:
SearchOptionsExplanationDC: dc: Find players by their data center.
SearchOptionsExplanationDefault: (default): Search by name if no option is provided.
SearchOptionsExplanationFC: fc: Find players in a specific Free Company.
SearchOptionsExplanationGender: gender: Search for players by character gender.
SearchOptionsExplanationNotes: notes: Look for players with specific notes.
SearchOptionsExplanationRace: race: Search for players with by character race.
SearchOptionsExplanationTags: tags: Search for players with specific tags.
SearchOptionsExplanationWorld: world: Find players by their home world.
SignUpTest: Sign up for test releases to help find bugs before they go live.
SocialListAddPlayersHelpText: This will add players found on social lists to PlayerTrack. With this unchecked, only players already in your list will be updated.
SocialListDefaultCategoryHelpText: Assign a category of your choosing when a new player is added to a social list. The player won't be automatically removed if they leave the social list.
SocialListSyncCategoryHelpText: Keep list automatically synced with a category. These are special categories that you can't add/remove from manually.
SocialListWarning: Social Lists update at specific times. All lists will refresh when you open their respective screen. In addition, the Friends and Blacklist will update on login. For large Free Companies, ensure you open and fully load each of the three pages in the bottom right to update the list.
StableExperience: This helps ensure a stable experience for everyone.
UnassignCategoryTooltip: click to remove category from this player
UnassignDynamicCategoryTooltip: This is a dynamic category and can't be manually unassigned.
WarningZone: Warning: This is the danger zone. These actions cannot be undone!
